<subSubSection id="B2EAE553529B0428D3E1AC64A0789E04" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="CB8EEA86A1E199EC70A8D09BE8D15553" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65344DBDFE772D877A785710ED4C296C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A slender fragile plant easily fracturing when dry. The leaves are usually with three oblong-elliptic leaflets, much broader than in 
<taxonomicName id="2353D1BF013D7C1DFDE3676274AEA876" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graniticola">
<emphasis id="6C575D0756B7D096F85148902631020D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea graniticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The sepals are quite variable and the tooth-like appendage is often reduced to little more than a swelling.
</paragraph>
